# LLM-Optimized Documentation

When implementing, debugging, or making decisions about a technology, **check the documentation first**. Many libraries now publish `llms.txt` or `llms-full.txt` files specifically designed for LLM consumption. Prefer these over guessing or relying on training data.

## How to Use

When you need documentation for a technology listed below:
1. If it has an `llms.txt` link, fetch it to get a structured index of all available docs
2. If it has an `llms-full.txt` link, fetch it to get the complete documentation in a single file
3. If it only has a "Best reference" link, fetch that for the most useful single-page reference
4. Use these docs to verify APIs, patterns, and best practices before writing code

